Package io.artframework.parser

Class ConfigParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.artframework.parser.ConfigParser
  • public final class ConfigParser
extends java.lang.Object
    The config parser is used to extract ConfigMap values from a string and returns a new config map with the values.

    The parser will use the following pattern to parse the given input.

      • accept

        public boolean accept​(java.lang.String input)
        Accepts the given input and creates a matcher from it returning the result of the match.

        The last input will be used when calling parse(). It is required to call accept before parse.

        Parameters:
        input - the input that should be parsed
        Returns:
        true if the config pattern matches and parse can be called

      • parse

        public ConfigMap parse()
                throws ParseException
        Parses the last input passed to accept(String) and returns the config map of this parser with the values from the given input.

        accept(String) must be called before calling parse.

        Returns:
        the ConfigMap with the values from the parsed input
        Throws:
        ParseException - if the given input cannot be parsed into the config map
